# Arkyt, Altai Republic

}}
Arkyt (; , ArkÄ±t) is a rural locality (a selo) in Kosh-Agachsky District, the Altai Republic, Russia. The population was 62 as of 2016. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Arkyt is located 141 km southwest of Kosh-Agach (the district's administrative centre) by road. Belyashi is the nearest rural locality.
